{"title_page": "Hostages (web series)", "text_new": "{{about|Hostages (web series) in India||Hostages (Israeli TV series)}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=August 2019}}\n{{short description|2019 Indian crime mystery thriller series}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Hostages\n| image                    = Hostages_Hotstar_Poster.jpg\n| caption                  = Hostages on Hotstar \n| genre                    = [[Mystery (genre)|Mystery]]<br>[[Crime (genre)|Crime]]<br>[[Thriller (genre)|Thriller]]\n| based_on                 = [[Hostages (Israeli TV series)|Hostages]] \n| creator                  = \n| director                 = {{ubl|[[Sudhir Mishra]]}}\n| presenter                = {{ubl|[[Hotstar Specials ]]}}\n| starring                 = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Ronit Roy]]\n* [[Tisca Chopra]]\n* [[Parvin Dabas]]\n* [[Aashim Gulati]] \n* [[Mohan Kapoor]] \n* [[Dalip Tahil]]\n}}\n| writer                   = {{plainlist|\n* Nisarg Mehta\n* Shiva Bajpai\n* Mayukh Ghosh\n}}\n| theme_music_composer     = Karel Antonin \n| composer                 = \n| country                  = India\n| language                 = Hindi\n| location                 = India\n| cinematography           = \n| editor                   = \n| network                  = [[Hotstar]]\n| picture_format           = [[HDTV]] [[1080i]]\n| released                 = \n| first_aired              = {{Start date|df=y|2019|5|31}}\n| last_aired               = \n| company                  = [[Applause Entertainment Limited|Applause Entertainment]]<br>[[Banijay Group|Banijay Asia]] \n| distributor              = [[Star India]]\n| executive_producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* Rohit Philip\n* Sameer Rajendran\n}}\n| producer                 = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Sameer Nair]]\n* Deepak Dhar \n* Deepak Segal\n}}\n| runtime                  = 25-33 Minutes \n| num_seasons              = 1\n| num_episodes             = 10\n| list_episodes            = #Episodes            \n| website                  = {{url|https://www.hotstar.com/1260005113|watch here}}\n| related                  = \n}}\n'''''Hostages''''' is an Indian crime thriller web video series directed by [[Sudhir Mishra]]. It is an official adaptation of an Israeli series [[Hostages (Israeli TV series)|of the same name]]. The series is streaming in seven Indian languages on [[Disney+ Hotstar]]<ref name=\"release2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.televisionpost.com/hotstar-to-stream-crime-thriller-hostages-from-31-may/|title=Hotstar to stream crime thriller \u2018Hostages\u2019 from 31 May|last=|first=|date=4 March 2019|website=live Mint|access-date=30 April 2019}}</ref> and stars [[Tisca Chopra]], [[Ronit Roy]], [[Parvin Dabas]], [[Aashim Gulati]] and [[Mohan Kapoor]].\nThe show has been renewed for a second season which is currently scheduled for premiere in May.<ref name=\"season2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/binge-watch/story/sudhir-mishra-on-hostages-2-lockdown-has-slowed-down-work-but-will-be-out-by-may-1666687-2020-04-14}}</ref> The show was also broadcast on [[StarPlus|Star Plus]] in April 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/current-affairs/coronavirus-lockdown-tv-channels-introduce-re-runs-of-shows-web-content-120032701406_1.html|title=\"Coronavirus lockdown: TV channels introduce re-runs of shows, web content\"|last=|first=|date=|website=Business Standard|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== Premise ==\nSurgeon Dr. Mira Anand (Tisca Chopra) is scheduled to perform a routine operation on the chief minister, but the night before the procedure, her family is taken hostage and she is ordered to assassinate her unwitting patient in order to save her family, forcing her to make a decision.\n\n== Cast ==\n\n* [[Ronit Roy]] as [[Superintendent of Police|SP]] Prithvi Singh [[Indian Police Service|IPS]]\n* [[Tisca Chopra]] as Dr. Mira Anand\n* [[Parvin Dabas]] as Sanjay Anand\n* [[Aashim Gulati]] as Aman\n* [[Mohan Kapur]] as Subramanian\n* [[Anangsha Biswas]] as Hyma\n* Sharad Joshi as Shovan Anand\n* Malhaar Rathod as Shaina Anand\n* Surya as Sharma Prince\n\n=== Recurring ===\n\n* [[Sachin Khurana]] as DYSP Dutt\n* Manish Uppal as Naveen Khatana\n* Parag Gupta as Bunty\n* Kashish Arora as Girl Hostage\n* Danish Kalra as Dr. Shastri\n* Harish Khatri as Dr. Hingoorani\n* Dalip Gulati as Doctor 1\n* [[Shahnawaz Pradhan]] as Shukla\n* Yusuf Hussain as Dr. Ali\n* [[Dalip Tahil]] as CM Khushwant Lal Handa\n* Richa Goswami as Avantika (CM\u2019S Secretary)\n* Saajan Malhotra as Rakesh (CM Security Guard 1)\n* Dayaram Yadav as CM Security Guard 2\n* Sumit Yadav as Arms Dealer\n* Bhavesh Babani as Sameer Kapoor\n* [[Palak Sidhwani]] as Min (Shovan\u2019S Crush)\n* Meenal Kapoor as Sneha (Head Nurse)\n* [[Amit Sial]] as Peter George (Morgue Incharge)\n* Ritu as Mishra Lata (Maid)\n* [[Manu Malik]] as Mahesh (Neighbour)\n\n== Promotion ==\nIt was announced as part of the [[Hotstar Specials]] in March. On May 18 the trailer<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hotstar.com/hostages-trailer/1000236005|title=Hotstar Trailer|author=Hotstar}}</ref> was released by [[Disney+ Hotstar]] on various social media platforms, revealing the show would be streamed on May 31.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/hotstar-is-producing-indian-remakes-office-criminal-justice-1192012|title=Hotstar to remake The Night Of|author=Hollywood Reporter Team|date=4 March 2019|work=The Hollywood Reporter|location=Mumbai|accessdate=18 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Episodes ==\n{{Episode table|released=y|background=#000000|overall=|title=|director=|writer=|airdate=|airdateR=|country=India|episodes={{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 1\n |Title           = Threat\n |DirectedBy      = {{ubl|[[Sudhir Mishra]]}}\n |WrittenBy       = Nisarg Mehta\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|df=yes|2019|5|31}}\n |ShortSummary    = A night before the operation of the Chief Minister of Haryana, Dr. Mira Anand, his surgeon, is held hostage along with her family by three masked men. \n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 2\n |Title           = Sabotage \n |DirectedBy      = {{ubl|Sudhir Mishra}}\n |WrittenBy       =Nisarg Mehta\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|df=yes|2019|5|31}}\n |ShortSummary    = It's not a usual day at the hospital. While the clock is ticking, she desperately searches for a way to buy time. It is revealed that the kidnappers have a fourth team member.\n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 3\n |Title           = Complications \n |DirectedBy      = {{ubl|Sudhir Mishra}}\n |WrittenBy       = Nisarg Mehta\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|df=yes|2019|5|31}}\n |ShortSummary    = At work, Mira has to deal with her old mentor's suspicion. Meanwhile, an angry neighbour shows up at the house. \n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 4\n |Title           = Gatecrasher \n |DirectedBy      = {{ubl|Sudhir Mishra}}\n |WrittenBy       = Nisarg Mehta\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|df=yes|2019|5|31}}\n |ShortSummary    = A new challenge presents itself and Prithvi must tie up the loose ends. As Mira and Sanjay debate over her kids' safety, an unannounced visitor arrives. \n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 5\n |Title           = Falling Apart \n |DirectedBy      = {{ubl|Sudhir Mishra}}\n |WrittenBy       = Nisarg Mehta\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|df=yes|2019|5|31}}\n |ShortSummary    = As Mira struggles to help a wounded Sanjay, Prithvi takes a gamble to save the day. Meanwhile, suspicion creeps into the kidnappers' team. \n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 6\n |Title           = Pieces of the Puzzle \n |DirectedBy      = {{ubl|Sudhir Mishra}}\n |WrittenBy       = Nisarg Mehta\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|df=yes|2019|5|31}}\n |ShortSummary    =  A sudden order to be present at the station leaves Prithvi concerned. On her way to the hospital, Mira begins to penetrate Prithvi's identity.\n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 7\n |Title           = Betrayal \n |DirectedBy      = {{ubl|Sudhir Mishra}}\n |WrittenBy       = Nisarg Mehta\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|df=yes|2019|5|31}}\n |ShortSummary    =  Mira doesn't know whom to trust, especially after she discovers the truth about Sanjay. Meanwhile, Aditya hatches a plan to escape with Shovan and Shaina, with help from Mira. \n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 8\n |Title           = Escape\n |DirectedBy      = {{ubl|Sudhir Mishra}}\n |WrittenBy       = Nisarg Mehta\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|df=yes|2019|5|31}}\n |ShortSummary    = Prince and Aman chase Aditya and the kids into the jungle. Aditya meets with an accident and the kids are separated. Shaina calls the number provided by Mira earlier, and reaches Subramaniam, the CM's Chief of Security. At home, Sanjay does the unthinkable. \n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 9\n |Title           = Endgame \n |DirectedBy      = {{ubl|Sudhir Mishra}}\n |WrittenBy       = Nisarg Mehta\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|df=yes|2019|5|31}}\n |ShortSummary    =  Piecing together the clues, Mira is now following a new person. Elsewhere, Sanjay and Shovan take a risk to escape while Prithvi and Subramaniam end up in a clash after it is revealed that Subramaniam had recruited Prithvi. \n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 10\n |Title           =  A Matter of Choice \n |DirectedBy      = {{ubl|Sudhir Mishra}}\n |WrittenBy       = Nisarg Mehta\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|df=yes|2019|5|31}}\n |ShortSummary    = Prithvi has to contend with a mutiny from his crew, while Mira manages to turn the game around. Soon, she is faced with another choice, the one which was presented to her at the very beginning of the story. \n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}}}\n\n== Reception ==\nShweta Keshri of ''India Today'' enjoyed [[Hostages]] and feels it can't be ignored. Praising the acting of [[Ronit Roy]] and [[Tisca Chopra]], she said: \"It is intriguing in Most parts but lacks suspense in some parts\".<ref>\n\n== Accolades ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width: 99%;\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Award\n! Category\n! Recipient\n! Result\n|- \n| rowspan=\"4\" |2019\n|rowspan=\"1\"|[[iReel Awards]]<ref>{{Cite web |url= https://www.news18.com/i-reel-awards/list-of-nominees/#best_awards_5d691e3c111fdb8740e0d835|title=nominations|website=News18|accessdate=2019-09-11}}</ref>\n| Best Actor, Male (Drama)\n| [[Ronit Roy]] \n|{{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |[[Gold Awards]]\n|Best Actor (OTT)\n|[[Ronit Roy]]\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|Best Actress (OTT) \n|[[Tisca Chopra]]\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|Best Drama Series (OTT)\n|''Hostages''\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|9094282}}\n\n[[Category:Hotstar original programming]]\n[[Category:2010s Indian television series]]\n[[Category:2019 Indian television series debuts]]\n[[Category:Indian drama television series]]\n[[Category:Hindi-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Thriller web series]]\n[[Category:Crime thriller web series]]\n", "text_old": "{{about|Hostages (web series) in India||Hostages (Israeli TV series)}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=August 2019}}\n{{short description|2019 Indian crime mystery thriller series}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Hostages\n| image                    = Hostages_Hotstar_Poster.jpg\n| caption                  = Hostages on Hotstar \n| genre                    = [[Mystery (genre)|Mystery]]<br>[[Crime (genre)|Crime]]<br>[[Thriller (genre)|Thriller]]\n| based_on                 = [[Hostages (Israeli TV series)|Hostages]] \n| creator                  = \n| director                 = {{ubl|[[Sudhir Mishra]]}}\n| presenter                = {{ubl|[[Hots