 throughout.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/hostages-review-show-intrigues-can-t-hold-you-captive-throughout-102822|title='Hostages' review: The show intrigues but can\u2019t hold you captive throughout|last=Datar|first=Saraswati|date=1 June 2019|website=The News Minute|language=en-IN|access-date=2019-06-06}}</ref>\n\n== Accolades ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width: 99%;\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Award\n! Category\n! Recipient\n! Result\n|- \n| rowspan=\"4\" |2019\n|rowspan=\"1\"|[[iReel Awards]]<ref>{{Cite web |url= https://www.news18.com/i-reel-awards/list-of-nominees/#best_awards_5d691e3c111fdb8740e0d835|title=nominations|website=News18|accessdate=2019-09-11}}</ref>\n| Best Actor, Male (Drama)\n| [[Ronit Roy]] \n|{{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |[[Gold Awards]]\n|Best Actor (OTT)\n|[[Ronit Roy]]\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|Best Actress (OTT) \n|[[Tisca Chopra]]\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|Best Drama Series (OTT)\n|''Hostages''\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|9094282}}\n\n[[Category:Hotstar original programming]]\n[[Category:2010s Indian television series]]\n[[Category:2019 Indian television series debuts]]\n[[Category:Indian drama television series]]\n[[Category:Hindi-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Thriller web series]]\n[[Category:Crime thriller web series]]\n", "name_user": "2.30.91.105", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eReception:Added Content)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hostages_(web_series)"}
{"title_page": "St. David Catholic Secondary School", "text_new": "{{Infobox school\n| name                  = St. David Catholic Secondary School \n| image                 = StDavidCrest-2012.jpg\n| image_size            = 150px\n| caption               = \n| address               = 4 High Street\n| city                  = [[Waterloo, Ontario|Waterloo]]\n| province              = [[Ontario]]\n| postcode              = [[Postal codes in Canada|N2L 3X5]]\n| country               = Canada\n| coordinates           = {{coord|43.4843|N|80.5294|W|region:CA-ON|display=inline,title}}\n| schooltype            = Catholic (Separate Board)\n| religious_affiliation = [[Roman Catholic]]\n| founded               = 1965\n| schoolboard           = [[Waterloo Catholic District School Board]]\n| principal             = John Dietrich\n| grades_label          = [[Education in Canada#Levels in education|Grades]]\n| grades                = 9-12\n| enrollment            = 1045\n| language              = English\n| colours               = Green, Blue and White {{color box|green}}{{color box|blue}}{{color box|white}}\n| mascot                = Cedric\n| team_name             = Celtics (/selt(iks)/)\n| url                   = {{URL|https://stdavid.wcdsb.ca/}}\n}}\n\n'''St. David Catholic Secondary School''', established in 1965, is a [[Roman Catholic Church|Roman Catholic]] [[high school]] instructing students from grades 9 to 12. St. David CSS is located in [[Waterloo, Ontario|Waterloo]], [[Ontario]] and is a member of the [[Waterloo Catholic District School Board]]. Its building is the oldest secondary school building in the board.  Historically it was a junior high school, instructing students from grades 7 to 10. St. David received full funding from the Ontario [[Ministry of Education (Ontario)|Ministry of Education]] in 1985, when the school changed its educational focus to students in grades 9 to [[Ontario Academic Credit|OAC]]. Since the OAC year of secondary school was phased out of Ontario schools in the 2002-2003 school year, St. David CSS now teaches grades 9 through to 12. At present (2011) St. David educates 1045 students. St. David is named after [[St David]], a 6th-century saint.\n\n== Staff and administration ==\nAs of March 2016, St. David's principal is John Dietrich, with Daniel Hutter and Jacqueline Wettlaufer as [[Vice principal|vice-principals]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.wcdsb.ca/schools/schools_sda.html |title=Our Schools - St. David Catholic Secondary |work=wcdsb.ca|author= Waterloo Catholic District School Board|year=2011 |accessdate=14 October 2011}}</ref>\n\nThe school also has approximately 95 full-time teaching staff.\n\n== Uniform policy (2001 - 2002) ==\nAs with the other secondary schools in the Waterloo Catholic District School Board, St. David requires all students to wear a [[uniform]] every day, except for the occasional dress-down day (known to staff and students as \"Civies Day\"). During the 2001 - 2002 school year, this policy required all students to have [[Tennis shirt|golf]] and [[dress shirt]]s tucked into their pants at all times, on the basis that untucked shirts did not convey the proper sense of respect for the school.<ref>http://www.wcdsb.edu.on.ca/ap_memos/PDF/APC005.pdf</ref>\n\nDuring the last two weeks of June 2002, the administration of St. David made a public announcement that any student in violation of the uniform rules would be [[Suspension (school punishment)|suspended]] for one day. In Ontario, any disciplinary action of this type is listed on an [[student record|Ontario student record]], which may adversely affect a student's chances of acceptance to [[post-secondary education]]. Ontario student records also are investigated by teachers when reviewing students enrolled for classes, and by staff at other schools in the event a student applies for a transfer.\n\nNo prior violations of the rules were taken into account with this policy. Suspension, as a punishment, is typically given for much more serious academic and criminal offences. However, the provincial [[Safe Schools Act]] allows discretionary one-day suspensions for minor infractions of school policies and procedures. These suspensions cannot be formally challenged, as the Safe Schools Act does not allow for appeals of one day suspensions.<ref>http://www.wcdsb.edu.on.ca/ap_memos/PDF/APC012.pdf</ref> Nevertheless, the consequence would add to a student's record, causing any subsequent offenses within five years to be judged more harshly.<ref>http://www.wcdsb.edu.on.ca/info/safe/disciplinary_actions.html</ref>\n\nThe \"tucked-in shirt\" rule, though, was short-lived as at the beginning of the 2002 - 2003 school year, the policy was revised to eliminate the requirement of golf shirts being tucked in.\n\n[[File:St David HS Waterloo.jpg|thumb|right]]\n\n==Notable alumni==\n*[[Luca Congi]], kicker/punter for the [[Saskatchewan Roughriders]].  Congi was a member of St. David's senior [[Canadian football|football]] team in 2000 and 2001, in which years the team won the Waterloo County high school senior football championships, the first senior football championships in the school's history.<ref name=\"Brown\">Brown, Josh (July 29, 2006).  \"He's kicking into high gear\".  ''The Record'', Kitchener, Ontario: A1, A6</ref>\n*[[John Sullivan (football player)|John Sullivan]], safety for the [[Winnipeg Blue Bombers]].\n*[[Michael Latta]], [[National Hockey League]] player.\n\n== See also ==\n*[[List of Waterloo Region, Ontario schools]]\n*[[List of high schools in Ontario]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://stdavid.wcdsb.ca/ St. David Catholic Secondary School official site]\n* [http://stdavid.wcdsb.edu.on.ca/life/tour/index.html St. David school tour]\n* [http://www.wcdsb.edu.on.ca/ Waterloo Catholic District School Board]\n\n{{WDCSBSchools}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Saint David Catholic Secondary School}}\n[[Category:Waterloo Catholic District School Board]]\n[[Category:Catholic secondary schools in Ontario]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1965]]\n[[Category:Schools in Waterloo, Ontario]]\n[[Category:High schools in Waterloo Region]]\n[[Category:1965 establishments in Ontario]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox school\n| name                  = St. David Catholic Secondary School \n| image                 = StDavidCrest-2012.jpg\n| image_size            = 150px\n| caption               = \n| address               = 4 High Street\n| city                  = [[Waterloo, Ontario|Waterloo]]\n| province              = [[Ontario]]\n| postcode              = [[Postal codes in Canada|N2L 3X5]]\n| country               = Canada\n| coordinates           = {{coord|43.4843|N|80.5294|W|region:CA-ON|display=inline,title}}\n| schooltype            = Catholic (Separate Board)\n| religious_affiliation = [[Roman Catholic]]\n| founded               = 1965\n| schoolboard           = [[Waterloo Catholic District School Board]]\n| principal             = John Dietrich\n| grades_label          = [[Education in Canada#Levels in education|Grades]]\n| grades                = 9-12\n| enrollment            = 1045\n| language              = English\n| colours               = Green, Blue and White {{color box|green}}{{color box|blue}}{{color box|white}}\n| mascot                = Cedric\n| team_name             = Celtics (/selt(iks)/)\n| url                   = {{URL|https://stdavid.wcdsb.ca/}}\n}}\n\n'''St. David Catholic Secondary School''', established in 1965, is a [[Roman Catholic Church|Roman Catholic]] [[high school]] instructing students from grades 9 to 12. St. David CSS is located in [[Waterloo, Ontario|Waterloo]], [[Ontario]] and is a member of the [[Waterloo Catholic District School Board]]. Its building is the oldest secondary school building in the board.  Historically it was a junior high school, instructing students from grades 7 to 10. St. David received full funding from the Ontario [[Ministry of Education (Ontario)|Ministry of Education]] in 1985, when the school changed its educational focus to students in grades 9 to [[Ontario Academic Credit|OAC]]. Since the OAC year of secondary school was phased out of Ontario schools in the 2002-2003 school year, St. David CSS now teaches grades 9 through to 12. At present (2011) St. David educates 1045 students. St. David is named after [[St David]], a 6th-century saint.\n\n== Staff and administration ==\nAs of March 2016, St. David's principal is John Dietrich, with Daniel Hutter and Jacqueline Wettlaufer as [[Vice principal|vice-principals]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.wcdsb.ca/schools/schools_sda.html |title=Our Schools - St. David Catholic Secondary |work=wcdsb.ca|author= Waterloo Catholic District School Board|year=2011 |accessdate=14 October 2011}}</ref>\n\nThe school also has approximately 84 full-time teaching staff.\n\n== Uniform policy (2001 - 2002) ==\nAs with the other secondary schools in the Waterloo Catholic District School Board, St. David requires all students to wear a [[uniform]] every day, except for the occasional dress-down day (known to staff and students as \"Civies Day\"). During the 2001 - 2002 school year, this policy required all students to have [[Tennis shirt|golf]] and [[dress shirt]]s tucked into their pants at all times, on the basis that untucked shirts did not convey the proper sense of respect for the school.<ref>http://www.wcdsb.edu.on.ca/ap_memos/PDF/APC005.pdf</ref>\n\nDuring the last two weeks of June 2002, the administration of St. David made a public announcement that any student in violation of the uniform rules would be [[Suspension (school punishment)|suspended]] for one day. In Ontario, any disciplinary action of this type is listed on an [[student record|Ontario student record]], which may adversely affect a student's chances of acceptance to [[post-secondary education]]. Ontario student records also are investigated by teachers when reviewing students enrolled for classes, and by staff at other schools in the event a student applies for a transfer.\n\nNo prior violations of the rules were taken into account with this policy. Suspension, as a punishment, is typically given for much more serious academic and criminal offences. However, the provincial [[Safe Schools Act]] allows discretionary one-day suspensions for minor infractions of school policies and procedures. These suspensions cannot be formally challenged, as the Safe Schools Act does not allow for appeals of one day suspensions.<ref>http://www.wcdsb.edu.on.ca/ap_memos/PDF/APC012.pdf</ref> Nevertheless, the consequence would add to a student's record, causing any subsequent offenses within five years to be judged more harshly.<ref>http://www.wcdsb.edu.on.ca/info/safe/disciplinary_actions.html</ref>\n\nThe \"tucked-in shirt\" rule, though, was short-lived as at the beginning of the 2002 - 2003 school year, the policy was revised to eliminate the requirement of golf shirts being tucked in.\n\n[[File:St David HS Waterloo.jpg|thumb|right]]\n\n==Notable alumni==\n*[[Luca Congi]], kicker/punter for the [[Saskatchewan Roughriders]].  Congi was a member of St. David's senior [[Canadian football|football]] team in 2000 and 2001, in which years the team won the Waterloo County high school senior football championships, the first senior football championships in the school's history.<ref name=\"Brown\">Brown, Josh (July 29, 2006).  \"He's kicking into high gear\".  ''The Record'', Kitchener, Ontario: A1, A6</ref>\n*[[John Sullivan (football player)|John Sullivan]], safety for the [[Winnipeg Blue Bombers]].\n*[[Michael Latta]], [[National Hockey League]] player.\n\n== See also ==\n*[[List of Waterloo Region, Ontario schools]]\n*[[List of high schools in Ontario]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://stdavid.wcdsb.ca/ St. David Catholic Secondary School official site]\n* [http://stdavid.wcdsb.edu.on.ca/life/tour/index.html St. David school tour]\n* [http://www.wcdsb.edu.on.ca/ Waterloo Catholic District School Board]\n\n{{WDCSBSchools}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Saint David Catholic Secondary School}}\n[[Category:Waterloo Catholic District School Board]]\n[[Category:Catholic secondary schools in Ontario]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1965]]\n[[Category:Schools in Waterloo, Ontario]]\n[[Category:High schools in Waterloo Region]]\n[[Category:1965 establishments in Ontario]]\n", "name_user": "99.251.18.17", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eStaff and administration)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/St._David_Catholic_Secondary_School"}
